result.execSummary:
The defendant Nico Denay Tirado was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant must pay court costs and the cost of supervision.  DNA surcharge is assessed.  A DNA sample is required if not already provided.  Defendant is granted a Payment Plan of $25.00 per month beginning 1/3/17.  Failure to pay is 6 months jail consecutive.  Apply bond.
Defendant is granted huber for employment.  Do not report in late or under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances.  Absolute sobriety required.
